Read Logger File from SIGMA_SD900

Source: R/logger_SIGMA.R
readLogger_SIGMA_SD900.Rd

Read Logger File from SIGMA_SD900

readLogger_SIGMA_SD900(filepath, successOnly = FALSE, sep = ",",
  dateformat = .defaultTimeFormat("v6"))

Arguments

filepath

full path to input file
successOnly

if TRUE, only file entries with "SUCCESS" in column "-RESULT-" are returned. Default: FALSE
sep

column separator. Default: ","
dateformat

format of timestamp. Default: "%H:%M %m/%d/%Y"

References

http://www.hach.com/asset-get.download.jsa?id=7639983273

Examples

# set path to example file (contained in this package)
(filepath <- grep("SIGMA_SD900", exampleLoggerFiles(), value = TRUE))
#> [1] "/home/travis/build/KWB-R/kwb.logger/inst/extdata/SIGMA/example_SIGMA_SD900.csv"

# read the file
(samples <- readLogger_SIGMA_SD900(filepath))
